                        UNESCO World Heritage Site and one of the world's biodiversity hotspots.
                        <br>
                        Anamalai Hills are characterized by their lush green forests, cascading waterfalls, winding
                        rivers, and diverse flora and fauna. The name "Anamalai" translates to "elephant hills,"
                        reflecting the significance of the region as an important habitat for Asian elephants. Indeed,
                        Anamalai is home to several wildlife sanctuaries and reserves, including the Anaimalai Tiger
                        Reserve, Parambikulam Tiger Reserve, and Indira Gandhi Wildlife Sanctuary.
